result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany M. Jacobs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brittany M. Jacobs is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brittany M. Jacobs was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Conditions:

Attend, pay for, and successfully complete any assessments, treatments, or counseling directed by the agent.

Pay court costs.

Submit to AODA and follow through with treatment.  

Upon successful completion of probation, Defendant to be eligible for expungement per 973.015 and should follow up with the Clerk of Court regarding that procedure.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  15CM234 and 16CM6, both on the calendar for status today.  Counsel inform the Court that the parties have reached an agreement for resolution calling for def's pleas to counts 2 in both 15CM234 and 16CM6.  Def pleads no contest to both counts, both of which are for disorderly conduct.  Court's colloquy on pleas.  Finding of guilty.   Counsel address the Court re the parties' joint recommendation; asking for youthful offender treatment for expungement.  Sentence:  60 days jail, consecutive to each other, with huber.  Sentence is stayed for 2 years probation with conditions that she attend, pay for, and succ. complete any assts/treatment/counseling as directed by agent; pay one set of court costs; submit to AODA and follow through with treatment.  4 days jail credit in the event of revocation in 16CM6.
